title: Banks Retreat From Apartment Market - WSJ
text:
Property Report Banks Retreat From Apartment Market A pullback in lending is forcing builders to scramble for financing to finish projects; ‘I haven’t seen anything this seismically different since 2008’ By @LauraKusisto Feb. 21, 2017 7:00 a.m. ET 
Swelling supplies of apartment units are prompting big banks to pull back from new projects, forcing developers to scramble for capital, in a sign that the U.S. apartment industry headed for a downturn.
